When MHD_DIGEST_HAS_EXT_ERROR is defined but digest_ext_error(da) is a macro expanding to (false) (as shown in the provided definitions), the if controlling expression is a compile‑time constant false and therefore invariant. That makes the conditional always false, which violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 (controlling expressions shall not be invariant). If MHD_DIGEST_HAS_EXT_ERROR is not defined the whole #ifdef block is omitted and no violation occurs.
